{"id":209537,"date":"2023-11-07T22:21:27","date_gmt":"2023-11-07T22:21:27","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.ditchassist.com\/?page_id=209537"},"modified":"2023-11-07T23:58:29","modified_gmt":"2023-11-07T23:58:29","slug":"geo","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.ditchassist.com\/geo\/","title":{"rendered":"Image Georeferencer for Ditch Assist"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Import any image for map overlay in Ditch Assist by capturing a screenshot of your preferred map, such as cut-fill, elevation, or drainage design, and saving it as a JPG file. Utilize the georeferencing tool to create the required .jgw file for precise overlay on the map. Refer to the instructional video below for additional assistance.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n<title>Image Georeferencing<\/title>\n\n<script async defer src=\"https:\/\/maps.googleapis.com\/maps\/api\/js?key=AIzaSyAiwx1VASSXlgxLQ_Oi9U7bB1Z84aPXViM&libraries=places&callback=initMap\">\n<\/script>\n<style>\n    #map {\n      height: 600px;\n      width: 100%;\n    }\n#controls {\n  \/* position: fixed; This is removed to allow the controls to flow in the document *\/\n  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);\n  padding: 10px;\n  border-radius: 5px;\n  z-index: 1000;\n  margin-top: 10px; \/* Add some space between the map and the controls *\/\n}\n\n    .draggable {\n      position: absolute;\n      cursor: move;\n      z-index: 10; \/* Ensure the draggable element is above the map *\/\n    }\n    .resizeHandle {\n      position: absolute;\n      width: 10px;\n      height: 10px;\n      background-color: red;\n      cursor: se-resize;\n    }\n    #autocomplete {\n      width: 300px; \/* You can set the width as needed *\/\n    }\n<\/style>\n<\/head>\n<body>\n<!-- Location search and file input above the map -->\n<div id=\"location\"><input id=\"autocomplete\" placeholder=\"Enter a location\" type=\"text\"><\/div>\n<div id=\"map\"><\/div>\n<div id=\"controls\"><input id=\"imageUpload\" type=\"file\"> <button onclick=\"exportJGW()\">Export JGW<\/button> \n<script>\n    let map;\n    let overlay;\n    let imgBounds = {};\n    let imgWidth, imgHeight;\n    let fileName = '';\n\nfunction makeResizableDiv(div) {\n  const resizers = div.querySelectorAll('.resizeHandle');\n\n  resizers.forEach(resizer => {\n    resizer.addEventListener('mousedown', function(e) {\n      e.preventDefault();\n      const originalWidth = parseFloat(getComputedStyle(div, null).getPropertyValue('width').replace('px', ''));\n      const originalHeight = parseFloat(getComputedStyle(div, null).getPropertyValue('height').replace('px', ''));\n      const originalX = e.clientX;\n      const originalY = e.clientY;\n      const originalTop = div.offsetTop;\n      const originalLeft = div.offsetLeft;\n\n      function handleMouseMove(e) {\n        if (resizer.classList.contains('left')) {\n          const widthDelta = e.clientX - originalX;\n          div.style.width = originalWidth - widthDelta + 'px';\n          div.style.left = originalLeft + widthDelta + 'px';\n        } else if (resizer.classList.contains('right')) {\n          div.style.width = originalWidth + (e.clientX - originalX) + 'px';\n        } else if (resizer.classList.contains('top')) {\n          const heightDelta = e.clientY - originalY;\n          div.style.height = originalHeight - heightDelta + 'px';\n          div.style.top = originalTop + heightDelta + 'px';\n        } else if (resizer.classList.contains('bottom')) {\n          div.style.height = originalHeight + (e.clientY - originalY) + 'px';\n        }\n      }\n\n      window.addEventListener('mousemove', handleMouseMove);\n      window.addEventListener('mouseup', () => {\n        window.removeEventListener('mousemove', handleMouseMove);\n      });\n    });\n  });\n}\n\n    function makeDraggable(div) {\n      let offsetX, offsetY, initialMouseX, initialMouseY;\n\n      div.addEventListener('mousedown', function(e) {\n        \/\/ Correctly calculate the offset\n        initialMouseX = e.clientX;\n        initialMouseY = e.clientY;\n        offsetX = initialMouseX - div.offsetLeft;\n        offsetY = initialMouseY - div.offsetTop;\n        window.addEventListener('mousemove', handleMouseMove);\n        window.addEventListener('mouseup', () => {\n          window.removeEventListener('mousemove', handleMouseMove);\n        });\n      });\n\n      function handleMouseMove(e) {\n        \/\/ Use the initial offset to keep the position stable\n        div.style.left = (e.clientX - offsetX) + 'px';\n        div.style.top = (e.clientY - offsetY) + 'px';\n      }\n    }\n\nfunction initMap() {\n  const mapOptions = {\n    zoom: 2,\n    center: { lat: 49.6804, lng: -97.9236 },\n    mapTypeId: 'hybrid' \/\/ Add this line\n  };\n  map = new google.maps.Map(document.getElementById('map'), mapOptions);\n      initAutocomplete();\n}\n    document.getElementById('imageUpload').addEventListener('change', function(e) {\n      const file = e.target.files[0];\n      fileName = file.name.split('.')[0];\n      const reader = new FileReader();\n      reader.readAsDataURL(file);\n      reader.onload = function(e) {\n        const dataURL = e.target.result;\n        const image = new Image();\n        image.src = dataURL;\n\n        image.onload = function() {\n          imgWidth = image.width;\n          imgHeight = image.height;\n          const aspectRatio = imgWidth \/ imgHeight;\n\n          const imageOverlay = document.createElement('div');\n          imageOverlay.className = 'draggable';\n          imageOverlay.style.width = (200 * aspectRatio) + 'px';\n          imageOverlay.style.height = '200px';\n          imageOverlay.style.backgroundImage = 'url(' + dataURL + ')';\n          imageOverlay.style.backgroundSize = '100% 100%';\nimageOverlay.style.opacity = '0.55'; \/\/ 55% opacity\n\n          \/\/ Create draggable handles\nconst topMiddle = document.createElement('div');\nconst bottomMiddle = document.createElement('div');\nconst leftMiddle = document.createElement('div');\nconst rightMiddle = document.createElement('div');\n\ntopMiddle.className = 'resizeHandle top';\nbottomMiddle.className = 'resizeHandle bottom';\nleftMiddle.className = 'resizeHandle left';\nrightMiddle.className = 'resizeHandle right';\n\ntopMiddle.style.left = '50%';\ntopMiddle.style.top = '0';\nbottomMiddle.style.left = '50%';\nbottomMiddle.style.bottom = '0';\nleftMiddle.style.top = '50%';\nleftMiddle.style.left = '0';\nrightMiddle.style.top = '50%';\nrightMiddle.style.right = '0';\n\ntopMiddle.style.transform = bottomMiddle.style.transform = 'translateX(-50%)';\nleftMiddle.style.transform = rightMiddle.style.transform = 'translateY(-50%)';\n\nimageOverlay.appendChild(topMiddle);\nimageOverlay.appendChild(bottomMiddle);\nimageOverlay.appendChild(leftMiddle);\nimageOverlay.appendChild(rightMiddle);\n\n\n          makeResizableDiv(imageOverlay);\n          makeDraggable(imageOverlay);\n\n          map.controls[google.maps.ControlPosition.TOP_CENTER].push(imageOverlay);\n        };\n      };\n    });\n\nfunction exportJGW() {\n  const imageOverlay = document.querySelector('.draggable');\n  const rect = imageOverlay.getBoundingClientRect();\n  const mapDiv = document.getElementById('map').getBoundingClientRect();\n\n  const topLeftPixel = new google.maps.Point(rect.left - mapDiv.left, rect.top - mapDiv.top);\n  const bottomRightPixel = new google.maps.Point(rect.right - mapDiv.left, rect.bottom - mapDiv.top);\n\n  const topLeftLatLng = pointToLatLng(topLeftPixel);\n  const bottomRightLatLng = pointToLatLng(bottomRightPixel);\n\n  const pixelWidth = Math.abs(topLeftLatLng.lng() - bottomRightLatLng.lng()) \/ imgWidth;\n  const pixelHeight = Math.abs(topLeftLatLng.lat() - bottomRightLatLng.lat()) \/ imgHeight;\n\n  const jgwContent = [\n    pixelWidth,\n    0,\n    0,\n    -pixelHeight,  \/\/ Negative for north-up orientation\n    topLeftLatLng.lng(),\n    topLeftLatLng.lat()\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n\n  const blob = new Blob([jgwContent], { type: 'text\/plain' });\n  const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n  const a = document.createElement('a');\n  a.href = url;\n  a.download = fileName + '.jgw';\n  a.click();\n}\n\nfunction pointToLatLng(point) {\n  const scale = Math.pow(2, map.getZoom());\n  const proj = map.getProjection();\n  const topLeft = proj.fromLatLngToPoint(new google.maps.LatLng(map.getBounds().getNorthEast().lat(), map.getBounds().getSouthWest().lng()));\n  const x = point.x \/ scale + topLeft.x;\n  const y = point.y \/ scale + topLeft.y;\n  return proj.fromPointToLatLng(new google.maps.Point(x, y));\n}\nwindow.onload = function() {\n  initMap();\n};\n\nfunction initAutocomplete() {\n  const input = document.getElementById('autocomplete');\n  const autocomplete = new google.maps.places.Autocomplete(input);\n  autocomplete.bindTo('bounds', map);\n\n  autocomplete.addListener('place_changed', function() {\n    const place = autocomplete.getPlace();\n    if (!place.geometry) {\n      console.log(\"No details available for input: '\" + place.name + \"'\");\n      return;\n    }\n\n    \/\/ If the place has a geometry, present it on a map.\n    if (place.geometry.viewport) {\n      map.fitBounds(place.geometry.viewport);\n    } else {\n      map.setCenter(place.geometry.location);\n      map.setZoom(17);\n    }\n  });\n}\n<\/script> <\/div>\n<\/body>\n<\/html>\n\n\n\n<iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/player.vimeo.com\/video\/882248382?h=327f1f64f8\" width=\"800\" height=\"500\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Import any image for map overlay in Ditch Assist by capturing a screenshot of your preferred map, such as cut-fill, elevation, or drainage design, and saving it as a JPG file. Utilize the georeferencing tool to create the required .jgw file for precise overlay on the map. Refer to the instructional video below for additional [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-209537","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ditchassist.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/209537","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ditchassist.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ditchassist.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.ditchassist.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.ditchassist.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=209537"}],"version-history":[{"count":9,"href":"https:\/\/www.ditchassist.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/209537\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":209565,"href":"https:\/\/www.ditchassist.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/209537\/revisions\/209565"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ditchassist.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=209537"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}